# Constellation Planning Document Conventions

These conventions extend `markdown-ops-docs.mdc` for constellation-level planning and reporting documents.

## Document Metadata Block

Every constellation planning document starts with:

```markdown
**Date:** <DD Month YYYY>
**Author:** Constellation Manager (Senior Fleet Operations)
**Constellation:** <name and Walker notation, e.g., Aurora 53°:31/6/1>
**Shells:** <count and brief description>
**Coverage Requirement:** <e.g., 95% global between ±60° latitude>
**Classification:** Mission Operations — For Internal Use
```

## Coverage Analysis Format

Coverage analysis sections use this structure:

```markdown
### Coverage Analysis

| Latitude Band | Required Revisit | Achieved Revisit | Min Elevation | Gap Duration (max) | Status |
|---------------|------------------|------------------|---------------|---------------------|--------|
| 0°–30° N/S   | < 15 min         | 12.3 min         | 10°           | 8.1 min             | PASS   |
| 30°–60° N/S  | < 20 min         | 14.7 min         | 10°           | 11.2 min            | PASS   |
| 60°–80° N/S  | < 30 min         | 28.4 min         | 5°            | 24.6 min            | WATCH  |
```

Include:
- Per-latitude-band rows covering the constellation's coverage zone
- Required vs achieved revisit times
- Minimum elevation angle used in the analysis
- Maximum gap duration (longest period without coverage)
- Status: PASS, WATCH (within 10% of threshold), FAIL

