## Maneuver Campaign Plan Template

```markdown
# Maneuver Campaign Plan — <Campaign Name>

## Campaign Summary

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Objective | <e.g., Station-keeping correction for Polar Shell> |
| Campaign Type | <SK / Orbit-Raise / Phasing / Collision Avoidance / Disposal> |
| Affected Satellites | <list or "All in Shell X"> |
| Total Delta-V Budget | <X.XX m/s per satellite> |
| Campaign Window | <start date> to <end date> |
| Ground Stations Required | <list> |
| Criticality | <CRIT-1 / CRIT-2 / CRIT-3 / Nominal> |
| Approval Authority | <e.g., Flight Director + Constellation Manager> |

## Prerequisites

| Category | Requirement |
|----------|-------------|
| Conjunction Screen | Clear for campaign window (Pc < threshold for all targets) |
| Fleet Health | All affected satellites in Operational or Maintenance state |
| Ground Segment | Required stations confirmed available for commanding windows |
| Propulsion | Sufficient propellant margin for planned delta-V + contingency |

## Execution Timeline

| Phase | Start | End | Action | Satellites |
|-------|-------|-----|--------|------------|
| Plan  | T-7d  | T-3d | FD computes, uploads reviewed | All |
| Arm   | T-1d  | T-12h | Maneuver parameters uploaded, armed confirmed | Batch 1 |
| Execute | T-0 | T+2h | Burns execute at planned epochs | Batch 1 |
| Verify | T+2h | T+12h | Post-burn OD, delta-V assessment | Batch 1 |

## Rollback Criteria

Abort or defer the campaign if any of the following occur:
- New CDM with Pc >= 1e-4 involving any affected satellite
- Satellite enters safe mode or loses comm during arm phase
- Ground station outage reduces commanding coverage below minimum
- Space weather alert (Kp >= 7) during execution window

## Success Criteria

| Criterion | Threshold |
|-----------|-----------|
| Delta-V accuracy | Achieved within ±5% of planned |
| Post-maneuver orbit | Within altitude/drift tolerance |
| Fleet coverage | No degradation below SLA during campaign |
| Anomalies introduced | Zero campaign-induced anomalies |
```

## Cross-Reference Conventions

- Reference individual FOPs by full name: "see NOP_PROP_PREP_4_ORBIT-ADJUST_BURN"
- Reference fleet states using the state model defined in `constellation-operations.mdc`
- Reference standards by full designation on first use, abbreviated thereafter (e.g., "CCSDS 508.0-B (CDM)" then "CDM")
- Gap/issue numbering: G-<Campaign>.<N> with severity CRITICAL / HIGH / MODERATE / LOW
